title: Millburn High School girls tennis team gains title match
text:
Millburn High School girls tennis team gains title match October 9, 2015 Last updated: Friday, October 9, 2015, 12:47 PM By Jim Connelly Buy this photo staff photo by jim connelly 
Top-seeded Millburn High School aims to capture a 10th consecutive state sectional championship Tuesday, Oct. 13, when it takes on second-seeded West Windsor-Plainsboro South High School in the title match of the New Jersey State Interscholastic Athletic Association North Jersey, Section 2, Group 3 Tournament final. 
The match is scheduled for 2 p.m. at Millburn High School. 
The Millers defeated fifth-seeded West Morris Mendham High School 4-1 and West Windsor-Plainsboro South edged third-seeded Chatham 3-2 Oct. 8 in the section semifinals. 
Stephanie Schrage (first singles), Joanna Atwater (third singles), Isabella Waung and Sydney Zirlin (first doubles) and Elizabeth Gray and Anna Mandel (second doubles) accounted for Millburn's points. 
The section titlist advances to compete in the NJSIAA Group 3 semifinals Thursday, Oct. 15, at Mercer County Park in West Windsor. 
The group semifinals, pitting the North 1 champion against the North 2 champion and the Central Jersey winner against the South Jersey champion are scheduled for 9 a.m. 
The Group 3 championship match, with a berth in the following week's NJSIAA Tournament of Champions, is scheduled for Oct. 15 at 1 p.m. 
Editor's note: see the Thursday, Oct. 15, 2015, print edition of The Item of Millburn and Short Hills for more details.
